        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-05-31 15:25:52.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Have you done deployments in an OOM environment with a cluster APPC\n > (3 instances) setup?\n\nNo.\n\nI was working on CDT connection with APPC.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "99fad0a1fe0a436fbcdc5a10aced4483195087bd",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2535,
          "name": "Mayank Gupta",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "mayank.gupta@amdocs.com",
          "username": "mayankg2703"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-05-31 15:37:58.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nHi Patrick,\n\nPlease find problem and root cause of the problem.\n\n1.\tI find that application for cdt-proxy inside appc pod is listening at 9191. In service we exposed container port 9090. Because of that there will be no connection between appc and cdt application.\n2.\tWe can send port information inside any chart from parent chart. I think, there is no option by which we can use directly service.nodeport3 of appc values.yaml inside chart appc-cdt. Please find bellow changes to remove hard coded values.\n\ndiff --git a/kubernetes/appc/values.yaml b/kubernetes/appc/values.yaml\nindex 79991f5..a669d2c 100644\n--- a/kubernetes/appc/values.yaml\n+++ b/kubernetes/appc/values.yaml\n@@ -70,6 +70,8 @@ dgbuilder:\n   service:\n     name: appc-dgbuilder\n\n+appc-cdt:\n+  nodePort3: 32\n # default number of instances\n replicaCount: 1\n\n@@ -103,6 +105,11 @@ service:\n   nodePort2: 31\n   clusterPort: 2550\n\n+\n+  internalPort3: 9090\n+  externalPort3: 9191\n+  nodePort3: 32\n+\n\n\n+++ b/kubernetes/appc/charts/appc-cdt/templates/deployment.yaml\n@@ -39,6 +41,8 @@ spec:\n             initialDelaySeconds: {{ .Values.readiness.initialDelaySeconds }}\n             periodSeconds: {{ .Values.readiness.periodSeconds }}\n           env:\n+          - name: CDT_PORT\n+            value: \"{{ .Values.global.nodePortPrefix | default .Values.nodePortPrefix }}{{ .Values.nodePort3}}\"\n           volumeMounts:\n           - mountPath: /etc/localtime\n             name: localtime\n\n\nPlease test above changes and do let me know in case of any help required.\n\nThanks,\nMayank Gupta",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "e2824a24356b9831c1658b3fca630b61c45e5321",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 49,
          "name": "Patrick Brady",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "patrick.brady@att.com",
          "username": "pb071"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-05-31 15:51:29.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThanks, I will try the changes.\n\nI think the reason the port is not functioning correctly is because there is a missing \"targetPort\" statement in the services.yaml file that I just noticed. Our port 8282 forward includes this statement, which is why that one is working.",
        "patchset_number": 3
